  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PREPARATION OF A HCFC PHASE-OUT MANAGEMENT PLAN
The Government of the Democratic People&#x2019;s Republic of Korea has developed a staged approach to comply with the adjusted HCFC targets agreed by the Parties. During stage I, the Government plans to
freeze the consumption of HCFCs by 1 January 2013 and meet the 10 per cent reduction in 2015. In line with the overarching strategy, the Government proposes to implement the following specific activities:
Demonstration Foam Production Conversion of HCFC-141b to Cyclopanten; UNIDO
Feasibility Study for Conversion of Refrigeration Equiment Production from HCFC-22 to HC UNEP
Feability Study to Determine the Plan for HCFC-22 Production Facility UNIDO
Development of Enforcement Measures of Laws and Regulations to Control HCFCs UNEP
Training of Customs Officers UNEP
Improvement of Recovery and Recycling scheme (R&amp;R) UNIDO
Institutional Strengthening for Monitoring &amp; Evaluation of Implementation of HPMP UNEP</narrative>
  </description>
